American adventurer Steve Fossett is set for a solo, non-stop flight around the globe in the GlobalFlyer, funded by Virgin Atlantic.
Facing challenges like an uncooperative jet stream, Fossett remains vigilant.
With a parachute for emergencies, he's prepared for the three-day endurance test.
Despite GPS malfunctions, Fossett remains optimistic.
The flight, expected to last 60-80 hours, aims to inspire aviation advancements.
Virgin Atlantic's Sir Richard Branson supports the project, hoping for future fuel-efficient planes.
Fossett's journey, closely monitored by spotters, showcases his daring spirit and determination.
